<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--BigRed     07-20 0172</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Big Red,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Show Horse Shot Near Billings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BILLINGS, Mont. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Big Red, a show horse whose movie credits
included ``Little Big Man'' and ``The Missouri Breaks,'' was shot
in his stable by an unknown assailant, the horse's owner said.
   Owner Earl Rosell said the horse was shot in the left shoulder
while it was in a barn behind his house last Friday. The horse,
suffering shattered bones in its shoulder, went into shock and was
put to sleep, Rosell said.
   The 33-year-old horse was featured in films including ``Little
Big Man,'' ``The Missouri Breaks,'' and the television movie, ``The
Legend of Walks Far Woman.''
   He also performed in commercials and participated in jumping
competitions. In Billings, he pulled Santa's sleigh at Christmas,
making visits to children in hospitals and other groups.
   Rosell said he doesn't understand why someone would have wanted
to shoot the horse.
   ``I don't think I have any enemies, and if I do, I don't think
they'd be bad enough to kill my horse,'' he said.
</TEXT>
