<HEAD>ATLANTA: General Noriega.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   As Democrats, we know who we are, and where we stand, and what
we seek.
   We are the diversity of America, committed to the ideal that all
of us can advance together _ and none shall be left behind.
   We are the party of change _ and across the generations, we have
seen what our country can become.
   We have never been willing to stand on the sidelines of history.
Whether the issue was war or peace, equality or justice, we have
been at the center of the struggle _ and sometimes we have known
our setbacks and paid a political price. We lost some elections,
but we never lost our soul. And now we know that the struggle has
made us stronger, as this country is ready to move again _ and we
are ready to lead.
   We are strengthened by a vigorous and honorable primary
campaign. We are strengthened by an extraordinary group of
candidates who this spring made all of us proud to be Democrats.
   We are strengthened by the example and the eloquence of one of
