commitment and not just geography. For Mike Dukakis and Lloyd
Bentsen, like John Kennedy and Lyndon Johnson, believe that we
cannot be content with things as they are _ that there is a newer
frontier to be crossed _ and a greater society to be built.
   After eight years of complacency and indifference, of problems
untended and pains untreated, it is time to restore purpose and
principle to America.
