<HEAD>Billy Graham Says Robertson Should Have Remained a Minister</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Rev. Billy Graham cited Jesse Jackson and Pat
Robertson as examples of how members of the clergy should and
should not campaign for public office.
   Jackson's presidential candidacy has demonstrated that clergymen
can seek public office and take strong moral stands without
mingling religion with politics, Graham said Tuesday.
   On the other hand, he said: ``If Pat Robertson made a major
mistake, it was when he renounced his ordination. I think even the
people who followed him, or people who didn't follow him, would
have a hard time understanding how a man could be called of God,
ordained of God _ and you're ordained for life _ and to renounce
it.''
   Robertson made an unsuccessful bid for the Republican
presidential nomination. Graham, who says he's not taking sides,
delivered the invocation at Tuesday's session of the Democratic
National Convention.
