<HEAD>Police Say 4-Year-Old Kills Babysitter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GULFPORT, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 12-year-old girl was shot to death by
the 4-year-old boy she was babysitting as the two played together,
police said.
   Rhonda Whitlock was pronounced dead at Gulfport Memorial
Hospital on Tuesday of a single .38-caliber gunshot wound to the
back.
   Police identified the 4-year-old as Whitlock's brother, but a
neighbor, Arlena Smith, whose children with to school with the
victim, said the 4-year-old was the girl's nephew.
   ``The 12-year-old and the 4-year-old were playing in their
mother's bedroom when the 4-year-old found a gun in the bed and
accidentally shot the girl,'' police Lt. Donald Thurman said in a
statement.
   The owner of the gun was not immediately known, police said.
