<HEAD>Pilot Killed As Plane Crashes in Swimming Pool</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTOLA VALLEY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A twin-engine plane crashed into a
backyard swimming pool, killing the 25-year-old pilot, a sheriff's
spokesman said.
   Neighbors said they saw the Beechcraft plane circling and heard
the engine sputtering before it plunged into the pool Tuesday night.
   The owner of the house and neighbors jumped in the pool and
tried to release the pilot from the plane. However, they could not
pry open the doors, a neighbor said.
   ``The plane was flying quite low, but then the engine sounded
rough. It went into a spin and didn't pull out,'' said the
neighbor, William Kunz.
   It is unclear whether the pilot died from impact or drowned,
sheriff's spokesman Sgt. Jeffrey Boyd said. The sheriff's
department would not release the name of the dead pilot, an Oregon
resident, until his relatives were notified.
   The National Transportation Safety Board was to investigate the
crash today.
