<1ST_LINE>r a PM-TeenSuicide     07-20 0186</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Teen Suicide,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teen Kills Self After Shoplifting Incident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AURORA, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 13-year-old boy who was accused of
stealing a 45-cent package of baseball cards shot and killed
himself an hour later, authorities said.
   The victim, who died in an Aurora hospital early Tuesday, was
not identified by police.
   The youngster was accused of shoplifting the baseball cards from
a convenience store near his Aurora home, said police Division
Chief Mike Stiers.
   A police officer summoned by the store's clerk issued the boy a
citation that ordered him to appear with a parent in court next
month. The officer then contacted the boy's mother.
   ``The next call we got was from the sister indicating that the
boy had shot himself,'' Stiers said.
   The boy apparently returned home, obtained a .22-caliber
revolver from a gun cabinet in a family room and shot himself in an
upstairs bedroom.
   ``It scares you, that's what it does, to think that a
13-year-old child resorts to that,'' Stiers said. ``Some way we
have to communicate to children that suicide's not a solution to
any kind of problem.''
</TEXT>
