<HEAD>Khomeini Talks to Iranians about Cease-Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini told his
people today that many of Iran's problems have been caused by its
resistance to United States' policy in the region, Tehran Radio
said.
   It was the first statement from Iran's 87-year-old spiritual
leader since Iran announced two days ago that it would accept the
year-old U.N. resolution calling for a cease-fire in the 8-year-old
Iran-Iraq war.
   Hashemi Rafsanjani, speaker of Iran's parliament and
commander-in-chief of Iran's armed forces, said it was Khomeini who
decided to accept the resolution.
   Khomeini had previously rejected all attempts to end the war,
saying Iran would continue fighting until Iraqi President Saddam
Hussein was overthrown.
