<2ND_LINE>PM-Parachute Jump,0172</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Men Parachute Off 40-Story Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three men parachuted off the roof of a
40-story building early today, polie said.
   The men were later traced by police to a hospital where one had
sought treatment for back injuries, and their parachutes were
confiscated, police said.
   No arrests were made. Lt. Gene LaBriola said the city attorney's
office will decide whether to file charges.
   Police said the jump took place about 1:30 a.m. from a building
on Wilshire Boulevard.
   ``It appears they did it for sport,'' said LaBriola.
   A security guard told authorities one of the three was injured
when he landed on a sidewalk. Officers went to the nearest medical
facility, the Hospital of the Good Samaritan, and found three men
with parachutes, LaBriola said.
   The men's identities were not immediately available, nor was the
extent of the one man's injuries, police said.
   ``It's a mystery how they got on the roof,'' LaBriola said.
