<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Fleeing Suspects,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspects Run _ Right Into Sheriff's Arms</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DELRAY BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four burglary suspects raced across
two county lines, abandoned their car on Interstate 95 and ran _
straight into a Palm Beach County Sheriff's substation.
   They left a North Miami used car dealership after a break-in
Tuesday in a 1988 four-door Oldsmobile, then ran out of gas in
Delray Beach, said sheriff's Sgt. Ken Deischer. They jumped a fence
and ran, he said.
   ``They didn't know this was the courthouse, let alone the
sheriff's office,'' Deischer said. ``They ran right to the
building.''
   Sgt. Mark Bannon was parked in back at 5 a.m. when he saw the
four men run into the parking lot. Another officer had radioed that
the suspects had run from their car minutes earlier, but Bannon was
still surprised.
   ``I looked up, and here they are,'' he said. ``I guess they
picked the wrong spot to bail out of a car.''
   The four were arrested and charged with burglary and grand theft.
