<HEAD>Cheese Hat Draws Attention at Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wearing a hat that resembled a large chunk of
cheese, Wisconsin delegate Tom Harnisch drew double-takes from
amused pedestrians on Atlanta's downtown streets Wednesday.
   ``I don't think it could be much more embarrassing to walk
around with your pants down,'' Harnisch said as he walked to a
hotel for a Democratic National Convention reception.
   But Harnisch, a former two-term Wisconsin state senator, said
all the stares and occasional snide comments were worth it.
   After all, Wisconsin is known as America's Dairyland, and his
home of Neillsville is in the 3rd Congressional District, which has
more dairy cows than people.
   ``Many people seem to know immediately that I'm from Wisconsin
because of the hat,'' Harnisch said.
   Others don't know what to make of the large, triangular-shaped
hat.
   ``They look at you like you're goofy,'' Harnisch said.
