<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Spain-Floods, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0692,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>At Least Nine Dead And 10 Missing In Spain Flooding</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout to UPDATE with 9 people dead, other details</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   
   SAN SEBASTIAN, Spain (AP) _ Torrential rains sent rivers over
their banks in northern Basque country, trapping motorists in their
cars and leaving at least nine people dead and 10 missing on
Wednesday, reports said.
   In the hardest-hit area of Guipuzcoa province, heavy rain fell
for four hours Tuesday night, knocking out power lines and blocking
roads, Spanish National Radio said.
   Police divers recovered some bodies inside submerged cars, civil
defense officials said.
   In some areas of the three Basque provinces, hail the size of
chicken eggs accompanied by 100 mph winds destroyed crops, causing
at least $9 million in damage, the radio said.
   Health authorities warned residents to boil all water before
drinking it because supplies could have been contaminated in the
flooding.
</TEXT>
