<1ST_LINE>u p AM-CVN--TVCoverage     07-20 0137</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-CVN--TV Coverage,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Scheduled Network Coverage of Democratic National Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a schedule of network coverage of the
Democratic National Convention for Thursday, all times EDT:
   ABC and NBC plan live, prime-time coverage of the convention
from 9-11 p.m. CBS will start at 8 p.m. All the networks say they
will adjust their schedules as news developments warrant.
   The major convention business during Thursday night's closing
session is Michael Dukakis' acceptance speech and the selection of
a vice presidential candidate.
   C-SPAN is carrying live, uninterrupted coverage of the session,
which is scheduled to begin Thursday at about 7:15 p.m.
   CNN also will cover the entire session, interspersed with
commentary and interviews.
   All the network morning shows are originating from Atlanta this
week, as are PBS' ``MacNeil-Lehrer NewsHour,'' ABC's ``Nightline''
and CBS' ``Nightwatch.''
</TEXT>
