<HEAD>Britain Will Keep Gulf Patrol Until Peace Assured</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Gulf Rdp</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Britian said Wednesday its four-ship patrol will
stay in the Persian Gulf to protect shipping until peace between
Iran and Iraq is certain.
   Foreign Office Minister David Mellor told reporters that Iran's
acceptance of the U.N. cease-fire resolution was ``great news,''
but added that the Royal Navy's Armilla Patrol will stay put until
``we are sure peace has broken out.''
   The patrol _ two frigates, a destroyer and a supply ship _
escorted 405 British-interest vessels in 1987 and about 300 in the
first five months of 1988, armed forces minister Ian Stewart said
in May.
