that chance.
   Michael Dukakis will have political partners like Jesse Jackson,
who in 1977, long before it was popular, went with me into the
Arkansas public schools to plead with the students to say ``no'' to
drugs, to ``open their brains and not their veins.'' Like Jesse
Jackson, Michael Dukakis has fought for drug-free schools with his
Governor's Alliance Against Drugs. Like Jesse Jackson, Michael
Dukakis knows it's not enough to urge our children to ``Just Say
No'' to drugs. They must be able to say ``Yes'' to life, too.
   Not long ago, police in Detroit broke the biggest crack ring in
that city. It was being run by two brothers from the Mississippi
Delta area of Arkansas. They had brought over 100 other young men
up from their home county to help them peddle dope.
