<HEAD>ATLANTA: peddle dope.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   The news reports said these country boys were more reliable than
the street-smart city kids. They gave a good day's work for a good
day's pay.
   The unemployment rate in the county these boys fled is almost 20
percent.
   For black teen-agers, it's more than twice that. Most farmers
and business people there are too broke to help get them off the
street. Those kids could make more money in a month in Detroit than
they could in a year back home.
   I wonder if their decision to deal misery for money would have
been different if President Dukakis had had eight years to make
good on his commitment to good schools and good jobs for all our
people in all our communities. I think they might have been able to
say ``No to drugs'' and ``Yes to life.''
   My friends, we are moving into a future which richly rewards
learning, achievement, and innovation. It punishes ignorance and
waste and the pursuit of short-term profits at the expense of
long-term growth.
   We need a president who understands the future and its
challenges. Michael Dukakis does.
   This is one of those pivotal moments in our history. The issue
is not whether we move left or right _ it is whether we move ahead
or fall behind. It's impossible to stand still in the strong
currents of change which engulf us.
   In these times of change, the Democratic Party has a place for
all Americans who share our vision of the future and want to do
their part: Democrats, Republicans, and independents. Michael
Dukakis has proved he will reach out to bring us all together.
   The strength of his message rests on two simple but powerful
ideas.
   The first is that we are all in this fight for the future
together. Whether they know it or not, the future of the California
entrepreneur and the New York investment banker is tied to the
drought-stricken, debt-ridden farmer in North Dakota and he poorest
black school child in Mississippi.
   We're all in this together. The second idea is that we must be
willing to do what it takes today to guarantee our children's
tomorrow.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>MORE</NOTE>
</DOC>
