<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Taiwan-Earthquake     07-20 0151</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Taiwan-Earthquake,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Strong Earthquake Jolts Eastern Taiwan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake centered off the coast
of eastern Taiwan jolted the island Thursday morning. There were no
immediate reports of casulties or damage, the Central Weather
Bureau said.
   The earthquake struck at 7:15 a.m. (7:15 p.m. EDT Wednesday) and
registered a preliminary 6.4 magnitude reading on the open-ended
Richter scale, the bureau said. The epicenter was at sea 19 miles
southeast of the coastal city of Hualien in eastern Taiwan.
   The tremor was felt in the capital, where residents reported
their houses shook violently, the bureau said.
   The Richter scale measures ground motion as recorded on
seismographs. Every increase of one number means a 10-fold increase
in intensity.
   An earthquake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage in a
populated area. An earthquake of magnitude 7 is a major tremor
capable of widespread, heavy damage in populated areas.
</TEXT>
