<1ST_LINE>u p BC-CVN--MendezText     07-20 0443</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-CVN--Mendez Text,460</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the text of the second nominating speech
of Jesse Jackson delivered by Olga Mendez to the Democratic
National Convention Wednesday night.
   I have a job to do and a very pleasant one.
   I am Olga Mendez from New York.
   
   Saludos carinosos a todos los puertorriquenos donde quiera que
esten. A los dominicanos, cubanos y a mis hermanos en idioma y
cultura.
   (A lovely salute to all the Puerto Ricans, wherever they might
be. To the Dominicans, Cubans and to my brethren in language and
culture.)
   
   
   Mister chairman, my fellow Americans, my dear delegates,
   It is an honor to me this evening, an honor for me this evening,
to second the nomination of the Rev. Jesse Louis Jackson for
president of the United States of America.
   This _ this _ is doubly historic for me, when the first Puerto
Rican woman in the state of New York in the Senate can rise to
seconding nomination of the first black American man for the
highest position in the town.
   Coalition-building is the order of the day when I say to you:
America needs Jesse Jackson, and Jesse Jackson is good for America.
Historically, all our great leaders have had a vision as to where
the nation should go. Jesse Jackson understands the realities of
the 1980's. He has a vision of an America where no man, woman or
child is ever, is ever denied the constitutional rights because of
racial, cultural, linguistic, physical, economic or religious
differences.
   His vision encompasses all of us.
   We Puerto Ricans and Latino Americans are too often not
perceived as citizens because of differences in culture and
language. Jesse Jackson understands our reality. He includes us in
a common effort to eliminate poverty and ignorance.
   America needs Jesse Jackson, and Jesse Jackson is good for
America.
   Jesse Jackson is the most qualified person to spearhead the
completion of this unfinished agenda. He'll assure that all patches
of the American quilt are respected, kept in good repair and united
in a powerful unity.
   In his administration, the word ``American'' will mean all that
it was supposed to mean.
   America needs Jesse Jackson, and Jesse Jackson is good for
America.
   As president, Jesse will move this nation to greater heights, to
economic common ground based on respect for our differences, and
enjoyment of our similarities.
   My fellow Americans, my fellow Democrats, after long years _
eight years _ of the most corrupted Republican administration in
history, now, more than ever, Jesse Jackson is good for America.
   He is good for America.
   Jesse Jackson for president of the United States!
</TEXT>
