<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a transcript of the speech by Arkansas
Gov. Bill Clinton nominating Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis for
president at the Democratic National Convention Wednesday night.
   I'm honored to be here tonight to nominate my friend Michael
Dukakis for president of the United States.
   We, as Americans, have a lot riding on this election.
   We face big challenges.
   Big problems.
   Big opportunities.
   The fundamental fact of 1988 is that we can't take our
prosperity for granted anymore in this competitive world economy.
   We've got to work harder and smarter to preserve the American
dream.
   And that means we need new economic policies and new people
policies.
